OL,6,FDoctors had mistakenly concluded he
OL,7,Fwas experiencing panic attacks and
OL,8,Fsent him home.
OL,10,FJohnny's mother says prejudices like
OL,11,Fhis young age contributed to symptoms
OL,12,Fbeing missed and their concerns
OL,13,Fweren't listened to.
OL,15,FShe said: "They should've listened to
OL,16,Fus saying it wasn't anxiety. We know
OL,17,Fwhat anxiety looks like.
OL,19,F"They drew a lot of conclusions
OL,20,Fwithout looking at the worst case
OL,21,Fscenarios.
