OL,4,Cis a start but 'does not go far enough'
OL,6,FIt will give families the legal right
OL,7,Fto get a second opinion if they feel
OL,8,Fthey're not being listened to, and
OL,9,Fwill be carried out by an independent
OL,10,Fcritical care team in the hospital.
OL,12,FJulie and Melanie welcome Martha's
OL,13,FRule, but say it doesn't go far enough.
OL,15,FJulie said: "It's a start but it
OL,16,Fdoesn't have anything about seeing the
OL,17,Fnotes and challenging the errors that
OL,18,Fare in there. The main thing is having
OL,19,Fthe notes.
