OL,6,F"I was being told that everything was
OL,7,Ffine, so if Martha's Rule had been
OL,8,Fthere I wouldn't have known I'd needed
OL,9,Fto ask for a second opinion."
OL,11,FA spokesperson for NHS England said
OL,12,Fthe states that patients have the
OL,13,Fright of access to their own health
OL,14,Frecords and to have any factual
OL,15,Finaccuracies corrected, and that in
OL,16,Fthe circumstance of young children, a
OL,17,Fperson with parental responsibility
OL,18,Fwill usually be entitled to access
OL,19,Ftheir medical records.
